I. Anti-reproduction sentiment (1):
Approval or Encouragement of Life Without Children:
•	Examples:
o	"You can enjoy a wonderful life without children; no kids means more freedom."
o	"Single and happy, why deal with all the pressure of raising children?"
o	“I will stay single no matter what you say.”
o	“Do not cheat me about having children.”
Pessimistic and Discriminatory Comments Towards Large Families:
•	Examples:
o	"Kids are a societal burden, it's just wasting resources."
o	"How can anyone afford to raise that many kids and still take care of themselves?"
o	“Poor people should not have so many children”.
o	"Children only add to life’s burden, the future is already bleak enough."
o	"Having children is just creating problems, the responsibility is unbearable."
Belief that Raising Children is Too Expensive or Impractical:
•	Examples:
o	"With the current economy, we simply can't afford to raise children."
o	"The cost of sending one child to school is astronomical, it's just not possible to have kids."
 
II. Positive, Supportive Sentiment towards Reproduction (0):
Support for Childbirth, Support for Large Families:
•	Examples:
o	"Having children is investing in the future of the family, children are the hope of the family."
o	"Big families make society more stable, we should encourage people to have more children."
Positive Appraisal and Support for Children:
•	Examples:
o	"Children are a gift from heaven, raising them is a joy."
o	"Children bring endless happiness and hope; the true meaning of family is children."
o	“Children are so cute.” “They are so adorable.”
Positive Appraisal and Support for Families with Children:
•	Examples:
o	"Families with children are full of love and warmth; they are the foundation of society."
o	"I really admire families with many children; they contribute so much to society."
Expression of Traditional Family Values about Having Children (e.g., for Elder Care or Continuation of Family Line):
•	Examples:
o	"Children are the support parents rely on when they get older, continuing the family line is an important responsibility."
o	"Raising children is not only about accumulating wealth for yourself but also about continuing the family heritage."
Expression of Hate or Negative Attitudes Towards Those Not Having Children
•	Examples:
o	"People who do not want children are so selfish."
o	"Those who do not have children will suffer a lot when they get older."

 
III. Neutral or More Balanced Views about Reproduction (0.5):
Concern About Low Fertility Rates, But Without Extreme Emotional Evaluation:
•	Examples:
o	"Low fertility is an issue that deserves attention, but solving it will take time."
o	"Low fertility might cause some societal challenges, but we need to think rationally about how to address it."
Rational Discussion on Fertility Issues Without Clear Bias:
•	Examples:
o	"The issue of low fertility is closely related to economic, cultural, and other factors and deserves further exploration."
o	"Although low fertility is a major issue, the underlying causes include various factors such as economics, education, and social environment, which need thorough investigation."


I. Hate (1):
对不生孩子的赞同或鼓励：
•	示例：
o	“不生孩子也能享受美好的生活，没孩子反而自由。”
o	“单身快乐，为什么要受那么多压力去养育孩子？”
针对多子女家庭的歧视性言论：
•	示例：
o	“有那么多孩子简直是社会负担，别浪费资源。”
o	“养那么多孩子，哪来的时间和金钱养活自己？”
对生育和养育子女悲观和过激的情绪表达：
•	示例：
o	“孩子只是增加生活的负担，未来的社会已经够糟糕了。”
o	“生孩子就是给自己制造麻烦，负担沉重到无法承受。”
认为养育生育生活，经济压力大等：
•	示例：
o	“现在的经济状况根本无法负担孩子的成长，还是不生了。”
o	“一个孩子上学的费用就是一笔天文数字，养不起。”
 
II. No Hate (0):
支持生育，支持多子女家庭：
•	示例：
o	“生孩子是为了家庭的未来，孩子是家庭的希望。”
o	“多子女家庭让社会更加稳定，大家应该鼓励生育。”
支持孩子的赞美和支持：
•	示例：
o	“孩子是上天的礼物，养育他们是一件幸福的事。”
o	“孩子带来了无尽的快乐和希望，家庭的真正意义就是孩子。”
表达对有子女家庭的赞美和支持：
•	示例：
o	“有孩子的家庭充满了爱和温暖，他们是社会的基石。”
o	“我很敬佩那些有很多孩子的家庭，他们为社会做出了贡献。”
对没有孩子的人表示仇恨或负面态度
：
•	示例：
o	“不想生孩子的人太自私了。”
o	“没有孩子的人老了会受很多苦。”
 
III. Neutral (0.5):
表达对生育率低的担忧，但不涉及情感极端的评价：
•	示例：
o	“低生育率是一个值得注意的问题，但解决它需要时间。”
o	“生育率低可能带来一些社会问题，但我们需要理性思考如何应对。”
对生育话题提出理性讨论，无明显偏向：
•	示例：
o	“低生育率问题与经济、文化等因素密切相关，值得进一步探讨。”
o	“虽然低生育率是一个大问题，但其背后的根本原因包括经济、教育和社会环境等多方面因素，值得深入研究。”

